|Entry=Entailment
|Description=In a metaphor mapping, an entailment constitutes the inferences in the frame or frame in the target domain given the conditions and constraints placed on the frame or frame in the source domain; entailments constitute anything that falls out from an understanding of a metaphor as a whole given the constraints on its frames.
